Anne Howard (actress) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anne_Howard_(actress) 0 Anne Howard (March 18, 1925 – April 22, 1991), was an American actress. Howard was born in Chicago. She was married to Leonard Caulfield (died 1980); they had one daughter, Vicki Caulfied. Anne retired from acting in 1966, then became active in civic affairs. She died on April 22, 1991, in Los Angeles, California, of a cerebral hemorrhage. Anne_Howard ( March_18_,_1925 – April_22_,_1991 ) , was an_American_actress . Howard was_born in Chicago .
